<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-08-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-08-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1625">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/132.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Vice Consul <persName type="to">Coen</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-08-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your despatch 48, July 8. At request French Embassy, use your
                                influence to insure respect for Chanel’s life and property.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>